The '''Thornycroft family''' was a notable [[English people|English]] family of sculptors, artists and engineers,<ref>{{cite news|title=Hamo Thornycroft's Family|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1888/05/29/archives/hamo-thornycrofts-family.html|work=[[The New York Times]]|page=9|date=29 May 1888|accessdate=3 April 2009}}</ref> connected by marriage to the historic [[Sassoon family]]. The earliest known mention of the family is stated in [[George Ormerod]]'s ''History of Cheshire'' as during the reign of [[Henry III of England|Henry III]] in the 13th century, taking its name from a [[Cheshire]] hamlet.<ref>{{cite book|title=History of Cheshire|author=George Ormerod|author-link=George Ormerod|year=1876|edition=2nd|volume=Volume 3|page=370}}</ref> [[John Isaac Thornycroft|Sir John Isaac Thornycroft (1843–1928)]] was the founder of the [[Thornycroft shipbuilding company]].

