{{Infobox military person | name = Tomás Urbina | image = Tomas Urbina.jpg | birth_name = Tomás Urbina Reyes | birth_date = 1877 | birth_place = Congregación de Nieves, [[Ocampo Municipality, Durango]] | death_date = {{death date and age|1915|09|15|1877}} | death_place = Congregación de Nieves, Ocampo Municipality, Durango | serviceyears = 1910-1915 | rank = General | unit = [[División del Norte]] | battles = {{plainlist| * Battle of Tlahualilo * Storming of Durango * Battle of Mapimí * Battle of El Ébano }} }}
[[File:Urbina, Villa y Zapata en Palacio, Museo de la Ciudad de México, México D.F., México, 2013-10-16, DD 138.JPG|thumbnail|Tomás Urbina (left) nexto to [[Pancho Villa]] and [[Emiliano Zapata]]]] '''Tomás Urbina''' (c. 1877&ndash;1915) was a general during the [[Mexican Revolution]] who allied with [[Pancho Villa]] and [[Emiliano Zapata]].<ref name="Credo">{{cite book|url=http://www.credoreference.com/entry/routmex/urbina_tomás|title=Encyclopedia of Mexico: History, Society & Culture|author=Eva Tessler|publisher=Routledge|accessdate=2010-03-27}}</ref>
Lieutenant '''Tomas Urbina''' and his counterpart and fellow General [[Rodolfo Fierro]], have been cited as the two halves of Pancho Villa, Fierro representing his more violent side.<ref name="Katz98">{{cite book|title=The Life and Times of Pancho Villa |first=Friedrich |last=Katz|authorlink=Friedrich Katz |pages=221, 269–272, 328–329 |year=1998 |publisher=Stanford University Press |isbn=0-8047-3046-6}}</ref>
Urbina was executed by General Fierro under the accusation that he betrayed Pancho Villa during the ''Battle of El Ébano'' (Spanish: Batalla de El Ébano), a 72-day [[siege]] of the town of [[Ebano, San Luis Potosí|El Ébano in the state of San Luis Potosí]], where Urbina finally surrendered his forces to the [[Constitutionalists in the Mexican Revolution|Constitutionalist faction]], and allegedly received a sum of money for his surrender.
== In film == In the film ''[[Villa Rides]]'' (1968), Urbina was portrayed by [[Robert Viharo]].
==In Literature== Urbina is a major character in the novel, ''The Friends of Pancho Villa'' (1996), by ''[[James Carlos Blake]]''.
