{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2013}} {{Infobox football biography | name = Wim De Coninck | fullname = Willem Aloïs Elodie De Coninck | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1959|6|23}} | birth_place = [[Deinze]], Belgium | death_date = | height = | position = [[Goalkeeper (football)|Goalkeeper]] | currentclub = | clubnumber = | youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = | years1 = 1975–1987 | years2 = 1987–1993 | years3 = 1993–1996 | years4 = 1996–1999 | years5 = 1999–2000 | clubs1 = [[K.S.V. Waregem|Waregem]] | clubs2 = [[Royal Antwerp FC|FC Antwerp]] | clubs3 = [[K.A.A. Gent|AA Gent]] | clubs4 = [[R.S.C. Anderlecht|Anderlecht]] | clubs5 = [[Eendracht Aalst]] | caps1 = | goals1 = | caps2 = 118 | goals2 = 0 | nationalyears1 = | nationalteam1 = | nationalcaps1 = | nationalgoals1 = | manageryears1 = 2000–2001 | managerclubs1 = [[SC Eendracht Aalst|Eendracht Aalst]] | manageryears2 = 2001–2002 | managerclubs2 = [[Royal Antwerp FC]] }}
'''Wim De Coninck''' (born 23 June 1959) is a retired Belgian [[association football|footballer]].
During his career he played for [[K.S.V. Waregem]], [[Royal Antwerp F.C.]],<ref>[http://www.rafcmuseum.be/spelersarchief/spelersfiche.php Profile] – FC Antwerp</ref> [[K.A.A. Gent]], and [[R.S.C. Anderlecht]]. He participated in [[UEFA Euro 1984]], but did not earn any senior international caps in his career.
